1
00:00:04,472 --> 00:00:07,408
⟨To travel is to live⟩

2
00:00:07,475 --> 00:00:11,912
⟨The journey of two people that started in Osaka and ran through Tokyo→

3
00:00:11,979 --> 00:00:15,416
The end will come soon⟩

4
00:00:15,483 --> 00:00:17,418
(Luna) We are connected.

5
00:00:17,485 --> 00:00:20,921
(Misato) Dad! (Masayoshi) His condition has suddenly changed!

6
00:00:20,988 --> 00:00:23,924
⟨Luna faces her past that she has kept away from →

7
00:00:23,991 --> 00:00:26,927
My partner Ryoko is watching over me⟩

8
00:00:26,994 --> 00:00:31,999
⟨The final episode of “Tsukiyo Gourd” has begun⟩

9
00:00:34,001 --> 00:00:36,504
(Luna) Ma-kun! (Justice) Oh.

10
00:00:37,505 --> 00:00:41,942
(Sound of electrocardiograph)

11
00:00:42,009 --> 00:00:45,446
(Masayoshi) It seems that my blood pressure has risen rapidly.

12
00:00:45,513 --> 00:00:47,948
I'm calm with medication now.

13
00:00:48,015 --> 00:00:51,452
(Luna) It's not life-threatening, right?

14
00:00:51,519 --> 00:00:53,454
(Justice) Ah.

15
00:00:53,521 --> 00:00:54,955
(Luna) Yes.

16
00:00:55,022 --> 00:00:57,958
>> I was told that I had to take precautions and be hospitalized.

17
00:00:58,025 --> 00:01:00,461
Either way, I have surgery in 5 days.

18
00:01:00,528 --> 00:01:01,962
(Luna) Yeah.

19
00:01:02,029 --> 00:01:06,467
>> I heard it's a pretty difficult surgery?

20
00:01:10,971 --> 00:01:14,909
(Luna) I'll go home for now. >> Huh?

21
00:01:14,975 --> 00:01:17,411
That's enough, come see me.

22
00:01:17,478 --> 00:01:19,914
(Luna) I don't want to upset you.

23
00:01:19,980 --> 00:01:22,416
Please give my regards to your mother.

24
00:01:22,483 --> 00:01:35,429
♪～

25
00:01:35,496 --> 00:01:38,933
(Ryoko) Dad, I'm glad you're safe.

26
00:01:38,999 --> 00:01:42,002
(Luna) Well, for now.

27
00:01:43,504 --> 00:01:45,439
(Ryoko) Kafka?

28
00:01:45,506 --> 00:01:48,442
(Luna) This is the book that made me want to become a novelist.

29
00:01:48,509 --> 00:01:52,947
I happened to find it in my father's room when I was in elementary school.

30
00:01:53,013 --> 00:01:55,449
Then I became obsessed with writing →

31
00:01:55,516 --> 00:01:59,453
When I was in high school, I confided in my father.

32
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:02,957
I want to be a novelist in the future.

33
00:02:03,023 --> 00:02:05,893
But...

34
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:08,395
It was said at that time.

35
00:02:08,462 --> 00:02:11,465
``Literature cannot save people.''

36
00:02:13,467 --> 00:02:16,403
But I still can't give up.

37
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:20,908
When I was a medical school student, I applied for a literary award and won the grand prize.

38
00:02:20,975 --> 00:02:24,912
I used a pen name because I wanted to keep it a secret from my family →

39
00:02:24,979 --> 00:02:26,981
In the end, it was discovered.

40
00:02:28,482 --> 00:02:31,919
(Eisuke) [It's great to have good memories]

41
00:02:31,986 --> 00:02:36,490
[From tomorrow, switch things up and do what you need to do]

42
00:02:39,994 --> 00:02:42,997
(Luna) So I quit medical school and left home.

43
00:02:44,498 --> 00:02:46,934
(Ryoko) That's right...

44
00:02:47,001 --> 00:02:50,437
(Luna) If I was rejected that much, what would happen to me now→

45
00:02:50,504 --> 00:02:53,941
It's not really, but I can't reveal it.

46
00:02:54,008 --> 00:02:57,945
(Ryoko) I don't want to be denied anymore.

47
00:02:58,012 --> 00:02:59,947
(Luna) There is that too →

48
00:03:00,014 --> 00:03:03,450
I don't want to disturb my father's heart any further.

49
00:03:08,956 --> 00:03:12,393
(Ryoko) Thank you for talking to me.

50
00:03:12,459 --> 00:03:15,396
No matter what choice mom makes from now on →

51
00:03:15,462 --> 00:03:18,399
I support mom.

52
00:03:18,465 --> 00:03:21,402
(Luna) Thank you.

53
00:03:21,468 --> 00:03:27,908
📱(vibration sound)

54
00:03:27,975 --> 00:03:30,911
(Luna) Hello.

55
00:03:30,978 --> 00:03:32,479
Huh!?

56
00:03:33,981 --> 00:03:35,983
I understand.

57
00:03:37,985 --> 00:03:41,422
My father disappeared from the hospital.

58
00:03:41,488 --> 00:03:42,990
(Ryoko) Huh!

59
00:03:44,992 --> 00:03:47,428
(Misato) Ah, Luna!

60
00:03:47,494 --> 00:03:49,930
(Luna) Can I contact you? Haven't you got it yet?

61
00:03:49,997 --> 00:03:51,932
>>I just received a call→

62
00:03:51,999 --> 00:03:56,437
It's my last request that you let me love you just for one day today.

63
00:03:56,503 --> 00:03:58,939
(Luna) The last thing...

64
00:03:59,006 --> 00:04:03,877
(Masayoshi) I'm not in a normal condition, so if something were to happen...

65
00:04:03,944 --> 00:04:06,880
I wonder where it went...

66
00:04:06,947 --> 00:04:08,882
(Justice) It's me→

67
00:04:08,949 --> 00:04:12,886
When I visited him in the morning, I spoke with him for a bit.

68
00:04:12,953 --> 00:04:18,392
(Eisuke) [I might not be able to go home anymore]

69
00:04:18,459 --> 00:04:21,895
(Masayoshi) [Haha... What are you saying?]

70
00:04:21,962 --> 00:04:24,398
[There is no such thing]

71
00:04:24,465 --> 00:04:26,900
(Eisuke) [Masayoshi-kun]

72
00:04:26,967 --> 00:04:32,406
[If you only have a few days left to live→

73
00:04:32,473 --> 00:04:35,409
what do you do? ]

74
00:04:35,476 --> 00:04:36,910
[What? ]

75
00:04:36,977 --> 00:04:42,416
[I eat what I want →

76
00:04:42,483 --> 00:04:45,919
Don't go where you want to go

77
00:04:45,986 --> 00:04:47,921
(Luna) The worst.

78
00:04:47,988 --> 00:04:51,425
It's not a joke to worry about your mother!

79
00:04:51,492 --> 00:04:55,429
In the first place, how much trouble will it cause to the hospital if you just slip out without saying a word?→

80
00:04:55,496 --> 00:04:58,432
You should know best.

81
00:04:58,499 --> 00:05:01,435
I'll definitely find you and bring you back.

82
00:05:01,502 --> 00:05:03,370
(Ryoko) Huh... (Misato) How?

83
00:05:03,437 --> 00:05:07,875
(Luna) Ma-kun, can you help me? >> Of course what should I do?

84
00:05:07,941 --> 00:05:09,877
(Luna) Go home →

85
00:05:09,943 --> 00:05:12,946
Look for a place where that person is likely to stop by.

86
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:19,453
>> It's nostalgic, isn't it? How many years has it been since?

87
00:05:23,457 --> 00:05:24,892
(Ryoko) Ah.

88
00:05:24,958 --> 00:05:26,894
Here, here!

89
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:28,896
(Kominato) Ah, yes.

90
00:05:28,962 --> 00:05:32,900
(Ryoko) I thought you were good at finding people who came to you on request.

91
00:05:32,966 --> 00:05:34,902
>> Ah, I was at the store the other day...

92
00:05:34,968 --> 00:05:36,904
(Kominato) Ah, hello, I'm a former detective.

93
00:05:36,970 --> 00:05:40,908
Eh, this is an active detective who stayed up all night and was staked out until morning.

94
00:05:40,974 --> 00:05:43,911
(Ryoko) Huh? Is that so? Sorry. (Tamura) No.

95
00:05:43,977 --> 00:05:47,414
Noppy's father also takes care of my family.

96
00:05:47,481 --> 00:05:50,918
>> Do you have any idea where your father might stop by?

97
00:05:50,984 --> 00:05:53,921
There's a shopping street near here... (Tamura) Ah, I understand.

98
00:05:53,987 --> 00:05:56,423
>> Oh yeah? Well, let's go for now, shall we?

99
00:05:56,490 --> 00:05:59,993
(Luna) Thank you both.

100
00:06:03,931 --> 00:06:06,867
>> I tried hitting all the stores I go to, but they don't seem to be there.

101
00:06:06,934 --> 00:06:09,369
I also tried calling an acquaintance of my uncle.

102
00:06:09,436 --> 00:06:11,371
Everyone says they don't understand.

103
00:06:11,438 --> 00:06:14,374
(Luna) Ma-kun, is the time still okay? >> About an hour left.

104
00:06:14,441 --> 00:06:17,377
Was there anything that might be a clue?

105
00:06:17,444 --> 00:06:21,882
(Kominato) No, I couldn't find anyone in the shopping district either.

106
00:06:21,949 --> 00:06:23,884
(Tamura) Also to my mother→

107
00:06:23,951 --> 00:06:27,387
I asked the neighbors to ask about it.

108
00:06:27,454 --> 00:06:31,458
(Ryoko) Yeah? What is this?

109
00:06:35,963 --> 00:06:39,900
>> Wow, I heard this from my aunt.

110
00:06:39,967 --> 00:06:41,902
Avoid confusing the patient's name →

111
00:06:41,969 --> 00:06:44,905
He asked each person the origin of their name and tried to remember it.

112
00:06:44,972 --> 00:06:49,409
(Tamura) Come to think of it, your father's motto is "Look at people", right?

113
00:06:49,476 --> 00:06:59,920
♪～

114
00:06:59,987 --> 00:07:03,357
(Ryoko) Huh? What day is this?

115
00:07:03,423 --> 00:07:07,861
The day of surgery? (Luna) I hear the surgery is on the 15th.

116
00:07:07,928 --> 00:07:10,430
(Kominato) Huh? What is this?

117
00:07:11,932 --> 00:07:15,369
"Matsui Shoten Musashino Bunko".

118
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:17,371
Is it the name of the store?

119
00:07:17,437 --> 00:07:20,874
(Luna) This is a coffee shop near Mitaka that was loved by literary giants.

120
00:07:20,941 --> 00:07:22,876
(Ryoko) Yeah, but why Mitaka?

121
00:07:22,943 --> 00:07:25,879
(Luna) Mitaka is a place connected to Osamu Dazai.

122
00:07:25,946 --> 00:07:29,883
June 19th is the anniversary of Sakuramomo's death.

123
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:31,885
(Kominato) Is it a day to remember Dazai?

124
00:07:31,952 --> 00:07:34,388
(Tamura) Ah, I saw it on the news.

125
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:37,891
Fans of Osamu Dazai are going to visit his grave.

126
00:07:37,958 --> 00:07:42,396
(Ryoko) So, your father was also planning on going to pray?

127
00:07:42,462 --> 00:07:48,402
The surgery was on the 15th, so you decided to go ahead of schedule and go today?

128
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:50,404
(Luna) I'm not the kind of person who would do that.

129
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:52,906
(Masayoshi) No, I don't know.

130
00:07:52,973 --> 00:07:55,976
Well, uh...｡

131
00:07:57,478 --> 00:07:59,913
Ah, look, look.

132
00:07:59,980 --> 00:08:03,851
Uncle: I'm posting a series of essays here every other month.

133
00:08:03,917 --> 00:08:07,921
He talks a lot about the charm of literature.

134
00:08:11,425 --> 00:08:16,363
📱(vibration sound)

135
00:08:16,430 --> 00:08:18,365
(Tamura) Yes, yes.

136
00:08:18,432 --> 00:08:20,367
Huh!?

137
00:08:20,434 --> 00:08:22,369
I understand, thank you.

138
00:08:22,436 --> 00:08:25,873
About an hour ago, my mother told me about a neighbor →

139
00:08:25,939 --> 00:08:28,375
He said he saw his father on the Chuo Line platform.

140
00:08:28,442 --> 00:08:31,378
(Ryoko) Eh, Mitaka is on the Chuo Line, right?

141
00:08:31,445 --> 00:08:35,382
>> Go where you want to go and eat what you want to eat.

142
00:08:35,449 --> 00:08:38,952
(Ryoko) Let's go to Mitaka.

143
00:08:45,459 --> 00:08:49,463
>> Ah, then we'll try looking for it.

144
00:08:50,964 --> 00:08:53,901
(Ryoko) Ah, excuse me, I would like to ask you a question→

145
00:08:53,967 --> 00:08:56,403
I'm looking for this man.

146
00:08:56,470 --> 00:08:58,405
>> I don't know.

147
00:08:58,472 --> 00:09:02,409
(Kominato) Um, excuse me, have you ever seen this person?

148
00:09:02,476 --> 00:09:04,845
No, I don't think so. >> Isn't it?

149
00:09:04,912 --> 00:09:06,847
(Tamura) Have you seen this person around here?

150
00:09:06,914 --> 00:09:09,349
(Bubbly) I hope you find it soon.

151
00:09:09,416 --> 00:09:11,852
(Bubbly) Tell mom it's okay.

152
00:09:11,919 --> 00:09:14,855
Ah, but there's a group joining us today.

153
00:09:14,922 --> 00:09:18,859
It would be helpful if Kominato-san could be there.

154
00:09:18,926 --> 00:09:23,864
(Luna) Group: That's right... Can I have a shop please?

155
00:09:23,931 --> 00:09:26,366
>> Shito-kun will provide Luna-san with a lot of hospitality →

156
00:09:26,433 --> 00:09:28,869
If you have any questions, please contact me immediately.

157
00:09:28,936 --> 00:09:30,871
(Luna) Thank you. >> No...

158
00:09:30,938 --> 00:09:32,873
Now, please excuse me. (Luna) Please be careful.

159
00:09:32,940 --> 00:09:35,876
(Female) I saw it. (Ryoko) Eh! Is it true!?

160
00:09:35,943 --> 00:09:37,878
(Female) Yes, this is the person.

161
00:09:37,945 --> 00:09:41,882
Please pick up the toy that my child dropped earlier.

162
00:09:41,949 --> 00:09:46,386
I was in front of the bakery over there about 10 minutes ago.

163
00:09:46,453 --> 00:09:48,889
(Tamura) Thank you very much.

164
00:09:48,956 --> 00:09:52,392
(Ryoko) Dad is coming after all.

165
00:09:52,459 --> 00:09:54,461
(Tamura) Let's go.

166
00:09:57,965 --> 00:10:01,401
>> \I've never seen it before./ (Tamura) Thank you.

167
00:10:01,468 --> 00:10:04,471
>> I feel like I've seen him before... (Luna) Have you seen this person?

168
00:10:05,973 --> 00:10:08,976
>> I don't understand. (Luna) Sorry.

169
00:10:17,351 --> 00:10:23,190
>> I don't really know. (Luna) Thank you.

170
00:10:29,997 --> 00:10:32,432
(Tamura) Let's put some thought into it.

171
00:10:32,499 --> 00:10:35,002
(Ryoko) Wow, thank you!

172
00:10:48,015 --> 00:10:51,451
(Ryoko) Mama Roissant looks delicious.

173
00:10:51,518 --> 00:10:53,954
(Luna) Thank you.

174
00:10:54,021 --> 00:10:56,456
(Ryoko) I'm sure it's a croissant →

175
00:10:56,523 --> 00:10:59,459
It means crescent moon in French.

176
00:10:59,526 --> 00:11:02,963
(Tamura) The moon isn't out today.

177
00:11:03,030 --> 00:11:07,901
(Luna) It's Ariake's moon today, so it might come out in the middle of the night.

178
00:11:07,968 --> 00:11:12,906
(Ryoko) It's funny how the moon is called by different names depending on the day, even though there is only one moon.

179
00:11:12,973 --> 00:11:17,411
Upper string, lower string... What else?

180
00:11:17,477 --> 00:11:22,416
(Luna) Juzoya Komochizuki Jugoya→

181
00:11:22,482 --> 00:11:25,419
Twelfth night, waiting for the moon.

182
00:11:25,485 --> 00:11:27,921
(Ryoko) It's difficult.

183
00:11:27,988 --> 00:11:30,991
Number names are easy to remember.

184
00:11:38,498 --> 00:11:43,937
(Luna) Ever since I can remember, there's been a book that I've loved.

185
00:11:44,004 --> 00:11:47,941
Hans Christian Andersen's work is called ``A picture book without pictures.''

186
00:11:48,008 --> 00:11:51,511
(Ryoko) Hey, what kind of story is this?

187
00:11:54,014 --> 00:11:59,453
(Luna's voice) The moon appears to a lonely and poor young painter living in the attic.→

188
00:11:59,519 --> 00:12:03,890
We will tell you about scenes from around the world seen from the sky.

189
00:12:03,957 --> 00:12:06,893
Paris, Venice, India, etc.→

190
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:10,397
Sadness and joy of people living in various places →

191
00:12:10,464 --> 00:12:14,401
The scenery and customs of a foreign country where lovers part ways.

192
00:12:14,468 --> 00:12:17,904
A story of a distant world brought to you by the moon →

193
00:12:17,971 --> 00:12:20,907
Heal the hearts of young people, quietly →

194
00:12:20,974 --> 00:12:23,910
But it was deeply ingrained.

195
00:12:23,977 --> 00:12:27,914
(Ryoko) It's the moon that delivers stories.

196
00:12:27,981 --> 00:12:32,919
Ah, speaking of Andersen, when he first met his mom...

197
00:12:32,986 --> 00:12:35,422
(ルナ) 〔To travel is to live〕

198
00:12:35,489 --> 00:12:38,425
[These are Andersen's words]

199
00:12:38,492 --> 00:12:41,428
(Ryoko) Traveling is living.

200
00:12:41,495 --> 00:12:45,999
Those words changed my life.

201
00:12:47,501 --> 00:12:52,939
(Tamura) I too changed my life with the book Noppy lent me.

202
00:12:53,006 --> 00:12:54,441
(Luna) Huh?

203
00:12:54,508 --> 00:12:58,445
(Tamura) ``The Paradox of Youth'' was lent to me when I was having trouble with my parents' remarriage.

204
00:12:58,512 --> 00:13:00,447
Sakunosuke Oda's.

205
00:13:00,514 --> 00:13:04,384
That's what made me interested in Osaka.

206
00:13:04,451 --> 00:13:07,387
(Luna) That's right.

207
00:13:07,454 --> 00:13:12,893
📱(vibration sound)

208
00:13:12,959 --> 00:13:14,394
(Ryoko) Ah.

209
00:13:14,461 --> 00:13:17,397
(Luna) Yes, Kominato-san.

210
00:13:17,464 --> 00:13:19,900
📱(Kominato) Dad was found.

211
00:13:19,966 --> 00:13:21,902
(Luna) Huh?

212
00:13:21,968 --> 00:13:25,906
>> It's right in front of me.

213
00:13:25,972 --> 00:13:27,974
(Luna) Huh!?

214
00:13:29,476 --> 00:13:32,412
(Misato) Yes, I found it, thank you.

215
00:13:32,479 --> 00:13:35,415
Excuse me.

216
00:13:35,482 --> 00:13:38,418
Ha... Luna!

217
00:13:38,485 --> 00:13:43,423
(Misato) Ah~ I'm so glad I found it!

218
00:13:43,490 --> 00:13:46,927
(Tamura) Mr. Kominato is sending it to me now.

219
00:13:46,993 --> 00:13:49,930
(Ryoko) But why dad Marquee Moon?

220
00:13:49,996 --> 00:13:54,434
(Luna) Mom, did you talk? >> I can't believe he's not talking.

221
00:13:54,501 --> 00:13:57,938
(Luna) Then, Ma-kun? >> I'm sure you didn't say it was Mark-kun.

222
00:13:58,004 --> 00:14:01,441
📱(Vibration sound) (Luna) Then why...｡

223
00:14:01,508 --> 00:14:03,944
(Tamura) Ah, it looks like we've arrived.

224
00:14:05,445 --> 00:14:07,380
(Kominato) We've already arrived.

225
00:14:07,447 --> 00:14:09,883
OK? Don't you feel sick?

226
00:14:09,950 --> 00:14:11,885
(Misato) Dad!

227
00:14:11,952 --> 00:14:16,389
(Kominato) Looks like you're a bit drunk. (Misato) Eh, did you drink alcohol!?

228
00:14:16,456 --> 00:14:25,465
♪～

229
00:14:31,137 --> 00:14:35,008
Ha... I'm sleeping soundly.

230
00:14:35,075 --> 00:14:39,012
Kominato-san, thank you Bubbly-chan.

231
00:14:39,079 --> 00:14:42,015
Yes, but I was surprised.

232
00:14:42,082 --> 00:14:43,516
Really.

233
00:14:43,583 --> 00:14:46,019
(Ryoko) Dad, did you come to the store suddenly?

234
00:14:46,086 --> 00:14:49,022
>>Actually, I did it again...

235
00:14:49,089 --> 00:14:53,093
(Bubbly) [Thank you, take care and see you soon]

236
00:14:58,598 --> 00:15:00,533
[Hehehe…]

237
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:04,537
[Ah! Mr. Kobayashi for your reservation! ] [What? no…〕

238
00:15:04,604 --> 00:15:08,108
[Mr. Kobayashi has been waiting for you! Come in]

239
00:15:10,610 --> 00:15:15,048
(Bubbly) [I'm sorry~ This is a service, please.]

240
00:15:15,115 --> 00:15:17,050
[This is the shop's original cocktail]

241
00:15:17,117 --> 00:15:19,552
[My mom's recommended menu]

242
00:15:19,619 --> 00:15:22,622
[Unfortunately, I have a day off today.]

243
00:15:30,130 --> 00:15:34,501
[Ah, delicious] (Bubbly) [Ah, good!] ]

244
00:15:34,567 --> 00:15:38,004
(Eisuke) [Um... what about you? ]

245
00:15:38,071 --> 00:15:41,508
[Oh, my name is Bubbly]

246
00:15:41,574 --> 00:15:46,012
[Bubbly-san, is this long? ]

247
00:15:46,079 --> 00:15:48,515
[This is the 8th year]

248
00:15:48,581 --> 00:15:53,019
[I admire my mom and she is a truly wonderful person]

249
00:15:53,086 --> 00:15:56,089
(Bubbly) [Please also] [Ah, hello]

250
00:15:57,590 --> 00:16:00,026
(Akane) [Hey, look, my sister sent this]

251
00:16:00,093 --> 00:16:04,531
[That's the one I ate yesterday] (Meguru) [Melon parfait? Looks delicious! ]

252
00:16:04,597 --> 00:16:10,036
[Which shop is this? ] [Eh~ I didn't write the name of the store]

253
00:16:10,103 --> 00:16:12,539
(Meguru) [Bubbly-san, do you understand? ]

254
00:16:12,605 --> 00:16:14,541
(Bubbly) [Eh~ I don't know]

255
00:16:14,607 --> 00:16:17,043
[Oh no, it looks delicious] (Akane) [Hey~]

256
00:16:17,110 --> 00:16:31,624
♪～

257
00:16:33,126 --> 00:16:36,996
[Probably Parlor Amber]

258
00:16:37,063 --> 00:16:38,498
[What? ]

259
00:16:38,565 --> 00:16:42,001
[It has gold leaf on it, so it's the main store in Aoyama.]

260
00:16:42,068 --> 00:16:44,504
(Bubbly) [Amazing! You are very knowledgeable.]

261
00:16:44,571 --> 00:16:48,508
[The Yubari melon parfait here is exquisite]

262
00:16:48,575 --> 00:16:52,512
[We use melons purchased from contracted farmers in Hokkaido]

263
00:16:52,579 --> 00:16:55,014
[For the fresh cream, use Jersey cow's morning milk →

264
00:16:55,081 --> 00:16:57,016
It seems that he made it]

265
00:16:57,083 --> 00:17:00,520
[I feel like I'm starting to want to eat it.]

266
00:17:00,587 --> 00:17:05,025
[It's true, it fits! ] [Wow, that's amazing!] ]

267
00:17:05,091 --> 00:17:07,527
[Too amazing! ]

268
00:17:07,594 --> 00:17:10,029
(Eisuke) [Let's all go next time] (Bubbly and others) [I want to go! ]

269
00:17:10,096 --> 00:17:13,533
[Cheers to a great day, Bubbly-chan, Akane-chan, and Meguru-chan! ]

270
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:16,102
(Bubbly: Meguru: Akane) [Cheers! ]

271
00:17:19,105 --> 00:17:21,541
[Bub-chan, second helping haha…] (Bubbly) [Yes]

272
00:17:21,608 --> 00:17:23,042
[Ah!!]

273
00:17:23,109 --> 00:17:26,546
Sweets talk was fun.

274
00:17:26,613 --> 00:17:31,050
(Kominato) And after that, I suddenly felt drunk →

275
00:17:31,117 --> 00:17:34,554
I started falling asleep on the counter.

276
00:17:34,621 --> 00:17:38,124
Thank you very much for your help.

277
00:17:44,130 --> 00:17:47,066
The last place my dad said he wanted to go →

278
00:17:47,133 --> 00:17:51,137
...That was Luna-san's place.

279
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:57,577
When I heard that the success rate of surgery is 20% →

280
00:17:57,644 --> 00:18:01,581
I didn't know how to accept it.

281
00:18:01,648 --> 00:18:07,153
(Misato's voice) But it seems like your father has made up his mind.

282
00:18:08,655 --> 00:18:15,595
(Misato) But I want to believe that it will be successful...

283
00:18:15,662 --> 00:18:22,168
I've been confused and anxious every day.

284
00:18:30,176 --> 00:18:34,180
(Luna) I'm sorry for making you suffer by yourself.

285
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:39,552
>> Nope.

286
00:18:39,619 --> 00:18:43,056
Something makes me happy.

287
00:18:43,122 --> 00:18:47,126
It's been a while since the three of us were together as a family.

288
00:18:49,629 --> 00:18:54,133
Hey Luna, this isn't the last time, right?

289
00:18:55,635 --> 00:18:58,071
(Luna) It's absolutely fine.

290
00:18:58,137 --> 00:19:00,573
You're the type who won't die even if you kill him.

291
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:02,642
>> That's right.

292
00:19:05,645 --> 00:19:08,581
Oh Ryoko-san.

293
00:19:08,648 --> 00:19:11,584
(Ryoko) I bought a drink.

294
00:19:11,651 --> 00:19:15,588
Mom had tea and mom had coffee.

295
00:19:15,655 --> 00:19:17,590
(Luna) Thank you.

296
00:19:17,657 --> 00:19:22,095
(Ryoko) Ah, now that I think about it, in front of my mother's mother →

297
00:19:22,161 --> 00:19:26,599
There's something strange about calling your mom "Mama".

298
00:19:26,666 --> 00:19:30,103
>> I thought it was interesting too. (Ryoko) Aha.

299
00:19:30,169 --> 00:19:33,606
I guess I'll call you by name from now on.

300
00:19:33,673 --> 00:19:37,110
Oh no, I'm a little embarrassed.

301
00:19:53,126 --> 00:19:58,064
♪～

302
00:19:58,131 --> 00:20:00,066
(Luna) 《Patient's Notes...》

303
00:20:00,133 --> 00:20:02,068
(Justice) [Ask each person about the origin of their name →

304
00:20:02,135 --> 00:20:04,070
I tried to remember it]

305
00:20:04,137 --> 00:20:06,072
(Luna) 《Look at the people...》

306
00:20:06,139 --> 00:20:10,076
(Tamura) [Isn't your father's motto "Look at people"? ]

307
00:20:10,143 --> 00:20:11,578
(Luna) 《Numbers...》

308
00:20:11,644 --> 00:20:13,580
[Fifteenth Night, Sixteenth Night]

309
00:20:13,646 --> 00:20:16,583
(Ryoko) [Number names are easy to remember.]

310
00:20:16,649 --> 00:20:18,585
(Luna) 《I am a cat...》

311
00:20:18,651 --> 00:20:22,155
(Masayoshi) [He talks a lot about the charm of literature]

312
00:20:26,159 --> 00:20:28,161
(Luna) We are connected.

313
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:45,578
(writing sound)

314
00:20:46,346 --> 00:20:49,349
(Ryoko) Name of the character?

315
00:20:51,351 --> 00:20:54,787
Oh, they all have numbers!

316
00:20:54,854 --> 00:20:56,289
(Luna) Yes.

317
00:20:56,356 --> 00:20:59,792
(Ryoko) But Calico is a cat, right?

318
00:20:59,859 --> 00:21:04,797
(Luna) Since this is a novel where cats are anthropomorphized, Mikako is also a great character.

319
00:21:04,864 --> 00:21:09,302
This idea really reminds me of my father.

320
00:21:09,369 --> 00:21:12,739
(Ryoko) Does this mean it's the order of appearance?

321
00:21:12,805 --> 00:21:14,240
(Luna) Yes.

322
00:21:14,307 --> 00:21:17,243
First edition publication date, cat's death date, etc. →

323
00:21:17,310 --> 00:21:21,247
When it comes to numbers related to books, I have to go out of my way to look them up.→

324
00:21:21,314 --> 00:21:25,318
As for the characters, all you need is a book to solve the problem.

325
00:21:32,325 --> 00:21:37,764
(ルナ) ３ ８ １→

326
00:21:37,830 --> 00:21:43,836
０ ３ ８｡

327
00:21:49,509 --> 00:21:50,943
(Monitor) (Error sound)

328
00:21:51,010 --> 00:21:53,446
(Ryoko) Ah... (Luna) No?

329
00:21:53,513 --> 00:21:58,451
(Ryoko) Hmm... But there's still one more chance.

330
00:21:58,518 --> 00:22:00,453
(Luna) I'm starting to feel like I can't do it anymore.

331
00:22:00,520 --> 00:22:04,457
(Ryoko) Don't say things like that, let's look for it.

332
00:22:04,524 --> 00:22:09,962
This contains what dad wants to tell mom.

333
00:22:10,029 --> 00:22:13,399
I listened to a lot of stories about my father today→

334
00:22:13,466 --> 00:22:15,902
I thought that was definitely the case.

335
00:22:15,968 --> 00:22:19,906
So I won't give up.

336
00:22:19,972 --> 00:22:23,409
(Luna) Ryoko has guts.

337
00:22:23,476 --> 00:22:28,981
(Ryoko) I'll do whatever it takes to get mom's homework done.

338
00:22:30,483 --> 00:22:32,919
Hmm…｡

339
00:22:32,985 --> 00:22:39,992
I feel like I'm very close to finding the answer.

340
00:22:41,494 --> 00:22:45,998
The answer can be solved if you have a book...

341
00:22:49,001 --> 00:22:52,438
(Ryoko) Ha! Maybe...

342
00:22:52,505 --> 00:22:56,943
Mama last chance, can I try?

343
00:22:57,009 --> 00:22:59,946
(Luna) Huh? (Ryoko) Is it okay?

344
00:23:00,012 --> 00:23:08,955
♪～

345
00:23:09,021 --> 00:23:11,457
(Ryoko) Try typing this.

346
00:23:18,965 --> 00:23:25,404
(ルナ) ５ ３ ８ １→

347
00:23:25,471 --> 00:23:30,977
０ ３ ８｡

348
00:23:37,984 --> 00:23:40,419
(Luna) Ah! (Ryoko) Open!

349
00:23:40,486 --> 00:23:42,922
It's open! (Luna) That sounds like a lie!

350
00:23:42,989 --> 00:23:45,925
Ryoko: Where did the number "5" come from?

351
00:23:45,992 --> 00:23:49,428
(Ryoko) The answer was right in front of me. (Luna) Huh?

352
00:23:49,495 --> 00:23:53,432
(Ryoko) It is both the title of the book and a character →

353
00:23:53,499 --> 00:23:55,434
I.

354
00:23:55,501 --> 00:23:57,436
It has a "five" in it.

355
00:23:57,503 --> 00:24:02,008
(Luna) Ha! Amazing Ryoko genius! (Ryoko) Aha!

356
00:24:04,510 --> 00:24:06,512
Ah.

357
00:24:15,454 --> 00:24:17,457
(clicking sound)

358
00:24:22,862 --> 00:24:25,298
(Ryoko) This is...

359
00:24:25,364 --> 00:24:28,367
(Luna) The title of my novel.

360
00:24:31,370 --> 00:24:34,874
(Ryoko) What, what do you think of the book...?

361
00:24:37,376 --> 00:24:42,882
Dad, I read all of Mom's novels.

362
00:24:45,384 --> 00:24:49,822
(Misato) Yes, I finally figured it out.

363
00:24:49,889 --> 00:24:53,326
(Ryoko) Did your mother know what was inside?

364
00:24:53,392 --> 00:24:56,762
>> Somehow.

365
00:24:56,829 --> 00:24:59,765
📱 Inside my father→

366
00:24:59,832 --> 00:25:05,771
That was probably the only way to connect with Luna.

367
00:25:05,838 --> 00:25:09,775
Thank you, Ryoko-san.

368
00:25:16,349 --> 00:25:18,284
(Ryoko) Ah.

369
00:25:26,359 --> 00:25:30,796
(Eisuke's voice) ``In short, he is very well behaved.

370
00:25:30,863 --> 00:25:33,799
As a result, heat is difficult to transfer.

371
00:25:33,866 --> 00:25:39,372
I'm more interested in the skill of the composition than the depth of the story."

372
00:25:42,375 --> 00:25:46,812
(Eisuke's voice) ``I appreciate that you have an ambitious theme, but→

373
00:25:46,879 --> 00:25:52,885
The depiction of the characters' psychology leaves something to be desired."

374
00:25:54,887 --> 00:26:00,259
(Eisuke's voice) ``The structure of the introductory section was good, as it set expectations.

375
00:26:00,326 --> 00:26:06,832
That's why I was disappointed in the ending of the planned harmony.''

376
00:26:09,335 --> 00:26:11,771
(Eisuke's voice) ``The beauty of the writing is →

377
00:26:11,837 --> 00:26:16,275
On the contrary, I think it highlights his shortcomings.

378
00:26:16,342 --> 00:26:22,348
Merely having a high level of perfection is not enough to move people's hearts."

379
00:26:25,351 --> 00:26:29,288
(Luna) Huh~ Are you saying that much?

380
00:26:29,355 --> 00:26:49,308
♪～

381
00:26:49,375 --> 00:26:53,813
(Fragrance) If you're going up, it's on the right. If you're going down, it's on the left.

382
00:26:53,879 --> 00:26:55,314
(cough cough)

383
00:26:55,381 --> 00:26:58,751
(Fragrance) If you're going up, it's on the right. If you're going down, it's on the left.

384
00:26:58,818 --> 00:27:00,252
If you're climbing, the one on the right...

385
00:27:00,319 --> 00:27:04,256
(Atsushi) Are you going out yet? I got home late yesterday too.

386
00:27:04,323 --> 00:27:08,260
(Ryoko) I want to help my friend with some things.

387
00:27:08,327 --> 00:27:11,263
>> It's kind of emotional. I like it.

388
00:27:11,330 --> 00:27:13,332
(Ryoko) Emotional?

389
00:27:15,835 --> 00:27:20,773
>> Ah, okay, I'll make breakfast myself.

390
00:27:20,840 --> 00:27:22,775
Atsushi, help me.

391
00:27:22,842 --> 00:27:25,778
(Atsushi) Yeah~｡ Okay, hurry up!

392
00:27:25,845 --> 00:27:27,780
(Ryoko) Thank you.

393
00:27:27,847 --> 00:27:31,350
Well then, I'll go. (fragrance) Welcome!

394
00:27:34,854 --> 00:27:38,357
(Ryoko) If you like this, eat it with your mom.

395
00:27:42,361 --> 00:27:45,865
(Luna) Thank you for coming early in the morning.

396
00:27:47,366 --> 00:27:50,302
(Ryoko) Then I'll be at a nearby cafe.

397
00:27:50,369 --> 00:27:53,806
If anything happens, just call me and I'll be there all the time.

398
00:27:53,873 --> 00:27:55,808
(Luna) Yeah.

399
00:27:55,875 --> 00:28:40,352
♪～

400
00:28:49,361 --> 00:28:51,864
(Luna) Good morning...

401
00:28:54,366 --> 00:28:56,802
>>Ah ah...｡

402
00:29:03,909 --> 00:29:07,913
(Luna) When did you find out?

403
00:29:10,916 --> 00:29:18,357
>> I have ordered your family register in preparation for inheritance procedures.

404
00:29:18,424 --> 00:29:21,927
It happened just recently.

405
00:29:24,430 --> 00:29:29,368
If you search for the name "Luna Nomiya" →

406
00:29:29,435 --> 00:29:35,441
The profile of that store and you now has appeared.

407
00:29:40,880 --> 00:29:45,818
It's still slender.

408
00:29:45,885 --> 00:29:50,823
Are you eating properly?

409
00:29:50,890 --> 00:29:54,326
It's already a good year →

410
00:29:54,393 --> 00:29:59,398
Also think about your health.

411
00:30:01,901 --> 00:30:05,337
(Luna) I don't want you to say that.

412
00:30:05,404 --> 00:30:06,839
>> Huh?

413
00:30:06,906 --> 00:30:12,845
(Luna) Even though I'm about to have surgery, I end up drinking alcohol that I can't drink.

414
00:30:12,912 --> 00:30:15,848
As a doctor, what are you thinking?

415
00:30:15,915 --> 00:30:19,852
>> Hahaha…｡

416
00:30:19,919 --> 00:30:26,358
In the end, I just wanted to do what I wanted to do.

417
00:30:26,425 --> 00:30:28,360
Fufufu…｡

418
00:30:28,427 --> 00:30:30,362
(Luna) What is the last one?

419
00:30:30,429 --> 00:30:33,866
Could you please not end it on your own?

420
00:30:33,933 --> 00:30:39,438
>> Hehehe... Nothing has changed.

421
00:30:49,448 --> 00:30:53,953
(Luna) I opened the computer.

422
00:30:56,956 --> 00:30:58,958
>> I see.

423
00:31:01,460 --> 00:31:06,899
(Luna) Impressions of the work I read all of them.

424
00:31:06,966 --> 00:31:11,904
It was so spicy I felt dizzy.

425
00:31:11,971 --> 00:31:16,475
But I was really motivated.

426
00:31:18,978 --> 00:31:21,914
So →

427
00:31:21,981 --> 00:31:28,487
I would be in trouble if I left before you could praise me.

428
00:31:35,995 --> 00:31:40,366
(Luna) Even if I don't receive praise→

429
00:31:40,432 --> 00:31:42,935
Even if you hate me...

430
00:31:51,443 --> 00:31:54,380
(Luna) To you→

431
00:31:54,446 --> 00:31:56,949
I want you to be in this world.

432
00:32:06,959 --> 00:32:10,896
>> Nomiya Rana｡

433
00:32:10,963 --> 00:32:13,465
What is the origin of the name?

434
00:32:15,968 --> 00:32:19,405
(Luna) Someone's dark path →

435
00:32:19,471 --> 00:32:24,910
I wanted to be a shining light.

436
00:32:24,977 --> 00:32:32,484
Like the moon in the picture book without pictures that I received for my birthday.

437
00:32:36,488 --> 00:32:39,425
>> I see.

438
00:32:41,427 --> 00:32:45,931
That's a nice name hehehe...

439
00:32:52,438 --> 00:32:54,440
(Luna) Dad.

440
00:32:59,445 --> 00:33:02,881
(Luna) Me too...→

441
00:33:02,948 --> 00:33:05,451
Can I stay in this world?

442
00:33:10,456 --> 00:33:12,458
>> It's obvious.

443
00:33:14,460 --> 00:33:16,462
(Sound of sipping)

444
00:33:23,469 --> 00:33:25,404
>> Welcome back.

445
00:33:25,471 --> 00:33:27,906
Hahaha...

446
00:33:27,973 --> 00:34:22,394
♪～

447
00:34:22,461 --> 00:34:25,464
Looks like the surgery is over.

448
00:34:32,971 --> 00:34:39,344
(Eisuke's voice) ``Recently, I've changed my mind.''

449
00:34:39,411 --> 00:34:45,350
It was a mistake to say that literature cannot save people.

450
00:34:45,417 --> 00:34:50,355
When you are conscious of death, consider medical care and the law →

451
00:34:50,422 --> 00:34:54,359
I realized that there are limits.

452
00:34:54,426 --> 00:34:57,863
It is in the areas that these do not reach →

453
00:34:57,930 --> 00:35:01,867
The power of literature is demonstrated.

454
00:35:01,934 --> 00:35:07,372
Since I realized this, I have become a beloved literary giant across the generations.

455
00:35:07,439 --> 00:35:11,877
I started to have a deep sense of respect for him."

456
00:35:11,944 --> 00:35:13,879
My uncle developed it.

457
00:35:13,946 --> 00:35:16,882
(Eisuke) Thank you. (Masayoshi) You took a lot of pictures.

458
00:35:16,949 --> 00:35:20,385
(Eisuke's voice) ``The other day, just before Sakuramomo's death →

459
00:35:20,452 --> 00:35:23,889
I went to Zenrinji Temple in Mitaka.

460
00:35:23,956 --> 00:35:28,894
Opposite Dazai's grave is Mori Ogai's grave →

461
00:35:28,961 --> 00:35:30,896
On that tombstone →

462
00:35:30,963 --> 00:35:35,400
It says ``Rintaro Mori.''

463
00:35:35,467 --> 00:35:40,339
Ogai was neither a literary great nor a military doctor.→

464
00:35:40,405 --> 00:35:43,842
Name as just a human →

465
00:35:43,909 --> 00:35:46,845
He said he wanted to carve it."

466
00:35:46,912 --> 00:35:48,914
📱(vibration sound)

467
00:35:51,416 --> 00:35:53,418
(Kana's voice) "Understood."

468
00:35:54,920 --> 00:35:57,856
(Eisuke's voice) "Everyone is like him →

469
00:35:57,923 --> 00:36:03,929
All you have to do is proudly say, ``I am my own person.''

470
00:36:06,431 --> 00:36:11,370
(Eisuke's voice) "Be yourself."

471
00:36:11,436 --> 00:36:13,438
(Luna) Welcome.

472
00:36:21,446 --> 00:36:24,950
(Masayoshi) Okay... Ah, I'll open it. I'll open it.

473
00:36:28,453 --> 00:36:32,391
Congratulations from Luna on your retirement.

474
00:36:32,457 --> 00:36:36,461
I wish I could come see you. You're a shy person.

475
00:36:40,399 --> 00:36:44,336
That guy...hahaha...｡

476
00:36:44,403 --> 00:36:49,408
There are hints hidden in this book.

477
00:36:50,909 --> 00:36:54,846
(Eisuke) ``Moonlit Journey''.

478
00:36:54,913 --> 00:37:18,370
♪～

479
00:37:18,437 --> 00:37:20,872
(Ikematsu) I'm glad we decided on a good title.

480
00:37:20,939 --> 00:37:22,374
(Kikuo) Yes.

481
00:37:22,441 --> 00:37:24,876
Naoya Shiga's "Dark Night Journey" is also the basis →

482
00:37:24,943 --> 00:37:27,379
Apparently it had a different title at first.

483
00:37:27,446 --> 00:37:29,381
Huh? Is that so?

484
00:37:29,448 --> 00:37:34,953
It seems that Naoya Shiga also changed the title after reconciling with his father.

485
00:37:36,955 --> 00:37:39,825
(Ikematsu) Ah, thank you for your hard work.

486
00:37:39,891 --> 00:37:42,828
(Luna) Mr. Sawatsuji Mr. Ikematsu→

487
00:37:42,894 --> 00:37:45,330
Thank you very much for today.

488
00:37:45,397 --> 00:37:47,332
>>Thank you in advance.

489
00:37:47,399 --> 00:37:49,835
Mr. Luna Nomiya.

490
00:37:49,901 --> 00:37:53,405
(Luna) Yes, I'll get ready.

491
00:37:56,908 --> 00:37:59,344
>> Was it good?

492
00:37:59,411 --> 00:38:03,849
Throw away Sosuke Shigehara's name.

493
00:38:03,915 --> 00:38:06,351
I think it's good.

494
00:38:06,418 --> 00:38:08,420
It's starting again from here.

495
00:38:13,925 --> 00:38:16,862
(knock) (sound of door opening)

496
00:38:16,928 --> 00:38:20,365
(Ryoko) Excuse me! (Luna) Ryoko.

497
00:38:20,432 --> 00:38:22,868
(Ryoko) Yes, give me this.

498
00:38:22,934 --> 00:38:26,371
(Luna) Shinki's Saigyo Manju!

499
00:38:26,438 --> 00:38:28,874
A masterpiece loved by Toson Shimazaki.

500
00:38:28,940 --> 00:38:33,378
Did you go out of your way to buy it for me? (Ryoko) Yeah, I bought mine too.

501
00:38:33,445 --> 00:38:35,380
(Luna) Thank you.

502
00:38:35,447 --> 00:38:49,828
♪～

503
00:38:49,895 --> 00:38:51,897
(Ryoko) Luna.

504
00:38:53,398 --> 00:38:58,337
It's okay, I'm sure it'll work out.

505
00:38:58,403 --> 00:39:00,405
(Luna) Yeah.

506
00:39:07,913 --> 00:39:11,349
(Moderator) Thank you for joining us today.

507
00:39:11,416 --> 00:39:14,352
Let's take the stage right away.

508
00:39:14,419 --> 00:39:19,357
I'm Luna Nomiya, the author of ``Moonlit Journey.''

509
00:39:19,424 --> 00:39:21,860
(applause)

510
00:39:21,927 --> 00:39:23,862
(Tamura) Hey, it's here. (Applause)

511
00:39:23,929 --> 00:39:36,875
(Camera shutter sound) (Applause)

512
00:39:36,942 --> 00:39:38,810
Mom, that's cool. (Applause)

513
00:39:38,877 --> 00:39:42,314
The author's face is also nice. (Applause)

514
00:39:42,380 --> 00:39:45,384
(Camera shutter sound) (Applause)

515
00:39:47,385 --> 00:39:50,889
(Moderator) Now, please give your greetings.

516
00:39:54,893 --> 00:39:57,829
(Luna) I have just been asked to introduce →

517
00:39:57,896 --> 00:40:00,332
This is Luna Nomiya.

518
00:40:00,398 --> 00:40:02,334
(camera shutter sound)

519
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:06,338
(Luna) I like literature.

520
00:40:06,404 --> 00:40:09,841
I have always been saved by stories.

521
00:40:09,908 --> 00:40:14,846
Sad things and unreasonable things in life →

522
00:40:14,913 --> 00:40:17,349
There are many.

523
00:40:17,415 --> 00:40:24,356
Feeling hurt by someone's words or suffering from not being understood.

524
00:40:24,422 --> 00:40:28,860
But literature taught me.

525
00:40:28,927 --> 00:40:34,933
That everyone's life has equal value.

526
00:40:36,434 --> 00:40:40,872
I can stay here as I am.

527
00:40:40,939 --> 00:40:45,877
I want everyone to live their lives with such pride.

528
00:40:45,944 --> 00:40:52,450
I would be happy if this work could serve as a guide to that end.

529
00:40:54,953 --> 00:40:56,888
Finally →

530
00:40:56,955 --> 00:41:03,395
I was able to write this work thanks to a friend who traveled with me.

531
00:41:03,462 --> 00:41:09,467
Because of her, I was able to move forward.

532
00:41:11,970 --> 00:41:16,474
Please take this opportunity to express my gratitude.

533
00:41:18,476 --> 00:41:21,913
Ryoko.

534
00:41:21,980 --> 00:41:24,482
Thank you for meeting me.

535
00:41:28,486 --> 00:41:35,927
(applause)

536
00:41:35,994 --> 00:41:39,931
(Ryoko) ⟨I'm the one to say thank you⟩

537
00:41:41,933 --> 00:41:46,371
(Luna) [What kind of person was he? Ryoko's crush]

538
00:41:46,438 --> 00:41:47,873
[Here it is! ]

539
00:41:47,939 --> 00:41:49,374
[Birthday...]

540
00:41:49,441 --> 00:41:51,443
[It suits you very well]

541
00:41:52,444 --> 00:41:53,879
(Ryoko) [crying]

542
00:41:53,945 --> 00:41:55,881
(Luna) [To Ryoko →

543
00:41:55,947 --> 00:42:01,453
I want you to live a life where you can love your choices.]

544
00:42:05,457 --> 00:42:07,893
(Ryoko) ⟨Luna→

545
00:42:07,959 --> 00:42:13,965
Thank you for illuminating my life ⟩

546
00:42:17,969 --> 00:42:19,971
>> What!?

547
00:42:22,974 --> 00:42:25,410
(Kikuo) What do you mean? >> It was placed here →

548
00:42:25,477 --> 00:42:27,913
All of Nomiya-sensei's autographed books are gone.

549
00:42:27,979 --> 00:42:30,415
(Kikuo) Why are you doing this...?

550
00:42:30,482 --> 00:42:32,484
(Luna) Excuse me.

551
00:42:43,428 --> 00:43:32,911
♪～

552
00:43:32,978 --> 00:43:35,480
>> What are you doing? (Ryoko) Shi~!

553
00:43:39,417 --> 00:43:41,419
(Luna) We are connected.

554
00:43:42,921 --> 00:43:45,857
Ryoko: Let's go. (Ryoko) Yeah.

555
00:43:45,924 --> 00:43:48,360
(Luna) Excuse me. >> Eh, where?

556
00:43:48,426 --> 00:44:06,945
♪～
